phase1.code:
public class TwoDArrayExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // 2D array declaration
        int[][] matrix = {
            {1, 2, 3},
            {4, 5, 6},
            {7, 8, 9}
        };

        System.out.println("Row count: " + matrix.length);
        System.out.println("Column count: " + matrix[0].length);

        // Accessing elements
        System.out.println("Element at [1][2]: " + matrix[1][2]);

        // Printing the matrix
        System.out.println("=== Matrix ===");
        for (int row = 0; row < matrix.length; row++) {
            for (int col = 0; col < matrix[row].length; col++) {
                System.out.print(matrix[row][col] + " ");
            }
            System.out.println();  // New line after each row
        }

        // Creating a 2D array with different row sizes (jagged array)
        int[][] jagged = new int[3][];
        jagged[0] = new int[]{1, 2};
        jagged[1] = new int[]{3, 4, 5};
        jagged[2] = new int[]{6, 7, 8, 9};

        System.out.println("=== Jagged Array ===");
        for (int i = 0; i < jagged.length; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j < jagged[i].length; j++) {
                System.out.print(jagged[i][j] + " ");
            }
            System.out.println();
        }
    }
}

phase2.brokenCode:
public class TwoDArrayExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int[][] matrix = {
            {1, 2, 3},
            {4, 5, 6},
            {7, 8, 9}
        };

        // Wrong column length in loop
        for (int row = 0; row < matrix.length; row++) {
            for (int col = 0; col < 4; col++) {  // Should be matrix[row].length
                System.out.print(matrix[row][col] + " ");
            }
            System.out.println();
        }
    }
}

phase2.explanation:
The inner loop tries to access column 3 (index 3), but each row has only 3 columns (indices 0,1,2).

Always use matrix[row].length for the inner loop condition — never hardcode the column count!

Safe pattern:
for (int row = 0; row < matrix.length; row++) {
    for (int col = 0; col < matrix[row].length; col++) {
        // safe access
    }
}

phase3.solution:
public class MatrixPractice {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int[][] matrix = {
            {1, 2, 3},
            {4, 5, 6}
        };

        for (int row = 0; row < matrix.length; row++) {
            for (int col = 0; col < matrix[row].length; col++) {
                System.out.print(matrix[row][col] + " ");
            }
            System.out.println();
        }
    }
}
